items.name: Change-A-Character: Delinquent, Your Waifu Raises Hell In School!
items.description:
Note #1: For some reason, I'm having this Locon interact weirdly with some other Locon's... I'm not sure why yet but I'll see if I can figure it out (for example, it changed the color to grey for one). Seems to work fine with character specific ones though. Also, her holding weapons is super inconsistent, despite trying to train it on that to some extent :(.

Note #2: It generally aims for the "squat" position in anime delinquents. Just add standing if you want to change that.

What does it do you ask?

Your waifu used to be a straight A student but... Then she started hanging out with the wrong crowd and is now a delinquent! This Locon focuses specifically on the look of a delinquent as it portrayed in Japanese anime/schools, so expect that when working with the locon.

How to use it:

(I use Sampling Method DPM++ SDE Karras and Upscaler R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B).

0.6 to 1 depending on model/lora/etc combination.

Main Trigger

DelinquentT - For the her to become a delinquent.

standing, hand on hip - For a more aggressive standing pose.

squatting - For the delinquent squat.

Other Useful Tags

long skirt, pants, bandeau, hat, jacket on shoulders, chest sarashi, crop top overhang - Were common words used.

Anything Else You Want!

Extra, Extra!: Should be well trained and usable in most models. Images shown for example.

Picture Descriptions:

1-2: Hasaku with just this Lora.

3: AnythingV3 with just this Lora.

4-5: RevAnimated with just this Lora.

6: Hasaku combo'd with my in progress EvilV2 Locon.

7: Hasaku combo'd with my released Sheik Lora.

8: Hasaku combo'd with my released Tharja Lora.

9: Hasaku combo'd with my released Volume Lora.

How was it trained?

It was trained on animefull_final with 22 images with the usual self-pruning and tagging and a wide range of different images. I like keeping my prompts simple for the first few pictures so that you can see it without a whole bunch of mumbo jumbo. Make your pictures better than mine though!

What's next for this?

Probably needs an update but I've spent enough time on this one for now.

What's next that isn't this?

More character Loras. (Kanzaki Kaori and Musujime Awaki from the Railgun Series, Jill Valentine from Resident Evil, Echidna from Re:Zero, Rupee from Nikke, Spectre Tenebria from E7, Zephia from Fire Emblem Engage, Ivy from Soul Calibur 5, Heine from Combatants Will Be Dispatched, Conqueror Lilias from E7, Evelynn from LoL (base version), Laharl-Chan from Disgaea 5, Miku from Idaten Deities, Kuribayashi Shino from GATE, Rin Sohma from Fruits Basket, Kasumi from P5, Ikumi Mito from Food Wars, Alice Nakiri from Food Wars, Lulu from FF10, Laharl-chan from Disgaea, Dominique de Sade from Vanitas, and Dos from One Punch Man.) Grace

Character: Grace (Sound Voltex series)

Pixiv post here

Usage (Important!)

Note 1: This LoRA kinda sucks and I've been in pain trying to get this right for 3 weeks. I hope this somewhat works for you.

Note 2: put your negative embeddings immediately (if you have any) after putting stuff in NEG (this somehow improves chances)

I recommend 0.9, like this: <lora:SDVX_Grace_E5_prod1:0.9>

0.8~1.0 would usually do.

Prompts

Exceed Gear (variant with "double belt cover")

Mixxion

Replication Success Rate: A-

NEG: (exceed gear), gun, mechanical wings, microphone, bra

Sudde–ò Death

NEG: (exceed gear:0.9), microphone, gun, mechanical wings, (EG double belts:1.1), garter belt

NOTE: ideally fingerless gloves but yeah as explained above

Gravity Wars

Replication Success Rate: A

NEG: shorts, garter belt, microphone, gun, mechanical wings, gloves

Vivid Wave (Experimental and not thoroughly tested)

Replication Success Rate: ???

POS: pink eyes, (vivid wave), black skirt, garter straps, navel

NEG: (exceed gear:0.9), microphone, gun, mechanical wings

Other Notes

Disclaimers

Civitai thinks the Mixxion and Gravity Wars attire are R-18. While this is wrong, but they may be revealing. Be advised.

Be aware that the LoRA may cause suggestive content without explicit prompting. Never seen actual R-18 content while testing, though.

  • MeinaHentai [Top Pick]

  • AbyssOrangeMix3-A1

[VAE: blessed2]

Training Details

  • Trained on 5 different attire mentioned above as well as non-official attire.

  • Images were grabbed manually on pixiv with search query „Ç∞„É¨„Ç§„Çπ then handpicked.

  • Training data includes R-18 (excluding R-18G) content, but this LoRA is not intended to replicate R-18 content exclusively.

Tags were only partially pruned to improve flexibility of the LoRA (i.e. different, non-training data attire).

Therefore, you can mess with the prompts given here if you want to change attire. Not officially tested, but should be feasible.

items.name: DEN_MelkorMancin_Artsyle
items.description:
I don't think I do a good job with styles. I do something wrong in the text or data set choices, or maybe I just don't use enough consistent images. This was done with circa 100 consistent styled images.

This one has a strange love of the colour blue which you will see in the grid image and previews. Randomly some images just love to turn up in a blue monotone and I really can't understand that as nothing in the dataset looked close to this. Strangely I kind of like it but I haven't figured the negative prompt necessary to stop it, but I would love to control it more as I think this could work will if you can dictate the colour or gradient of the effect.

the sweet spot seems to be around 0.8 I think, and the results vary massively depending on the model you use. I have found the Babes checkpoint to produce best results, as it is complementary to the art style regardless.

modelVersions.name: v2.0
modelVersions.description:
Just trying to refine and improve. I'm not sure if a prefer the original or not, the new version maintains a better standard, but the original does create a more comic-esque style I enjoy.

I have found using the [From:To:When] prompt good for preventing the inversion from completely changing the image. If you make something you want to apply the style too try out [():DEN_melkorMK2:15] and it will create the base and start the style from step 15.

As ever i really want to see peoples work from these, so please upload and share.

Cute supporting character from a power fantasy isekai anime the anime isn't bad even if the premise sounds kind of bland and predictable at least the first season isn't I dropped it halfway into the second season because it lost the charm it once had and became like any other generic isekai harem anime.

As always have fun generating.
